body:
### Describe the bug

I want to use `@IfBuildProfile("dev")` to enable a Ressource only during local development (when dev profile is active).

So I have 2 variants of a resource, which creates a text/plain response

```
@DevOnly
@Path("/local")
class GenerateTokenResource {

    @POST()
    @Path("/token")
    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
    fun devToken() = Jwt.issuer("https://local.dev")
        .upn("jdoe@quarkus.io")
        .groups(setOf("User", "Admin"))
        .expiresIn(Duration.ofHours(15))
        .sign()

}

```

I wanted to test if this is working and I am using the non existent profile `dev2` for that.

```
@Target(
    AnnotationTarget.FUNCTION,
    AnnotationTarget.PROPERTY_GETTER,
    AnnotationTarget.PROPERTY_SETTER,
    AnnotationTarget.CLASS
)
@Retention(AnnotationRetention.RUNTIME)
@Stereotype
@IfBuildProfile("dev2")
annotation class DevOnly
```




### Expected behavior

I expect to get a 404 Not found exception

### Actual behavior

I am getting the String response

### How to Reproduce?

NOTE:

It works as expected when NOT using it via Stereotype

```
@IfBuildProfile("dev2")
@Path("/local")
class GenerateTokenResource {

    @POST()
    @Path("/token")
    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
    fun devToken() = Jwt.issuer("https://local.dev")
        .upn("jdoe@quarkus.io")
        .groups(setOf("User", "Admin"))
        .expiresIn(Duration.ofHours(15))
        .sign()

}
```

It does not work when using it via Stereotype

